mak to John Wesley Powell's triumphant narrative on exploring the Colorado River, from Walt Whitman's ode on crossing Brooklyn Ferry to Oscar Hammerstein's melodic tribute to Ol'Man River. More than fifty descriptions, meditations, and songs, with brief introductory notes, are balanced by sixty illustrations, including the elegant landscape paintings of Albert Bierstadt, the landscapes of Frederic Church, and the haunting photographs of Ansel Adams.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2021) 7aART / American / General.2bisacsh1 aAbbey, Edward, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAudubon, John James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBartram, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBradstrect, Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarson, Rachel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChamplain, Samuel de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClark, Ella E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClark, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCowie, Isaac, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCoxe, Tench, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDillard, Annie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrost, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGraves, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuthrie, Woody, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHakluyt, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHammerstcin, Oscar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.go